title: 13 Chess Books (gnv64)
description:
A collection of 13 chess books in PDF format:

01. Bishop v. Knight: The Verdict by Steve Mayer
02. Excelling at Chess by Jacob Aagaard
03. Mastering the End Game Volume 1 by Shereshevsky, Slutsky
04. Mastering the End Game Volume 2 by Shereshevsky, Slutsky
05. Multiple Choice Chess II by Graene Buckley
06. Paul Morphy: A Modern Perspective by Valery Beim
07. Practical Chess Analysis: A Systematic Method for Analyzing by Matk Buckley
08. Practical Chess Exercises: 600 Lessons from Tactics to Strategy by Ray Cheng
09. Secrets of the Russian Chess Masters Volume 2 - Beyond the Basics by Lev Alburt
10. The Complete Chess Workout: Train your brain with 1200 puzzles! by Richard Palliser
11. The Scotch Game Explained by Gary Lane
12. Theory and Practice of Chess Endings Volume 1 by Alexander Panchenko
13. Win at Chess: A Comprehensive Guide to Winning Chess for the Intermediate Player by Ron Curry
